{%- comment -%}
  Happie Custom: Fix unreadable white RTE links on blog articles.

  Root cause: css-bridge.liquid sets `--rte-link-color: var(--color-scheme-text)`.
  On the blog article template the scheme's text color is white, so every
  `.rte a` / `.inline-rte a` link inside the article body renders white-on-light
  and is unreadable. (Body paragraph text uses a different fixed dark color,
  which is why only links broke.)

  Fix: scope a readable brand color to article-page RTE links only — no
  effect on links anywhere else on the site.

  This lives in a standalone snippet (not in css-bridge.liquid) so it survives
  future Shopify theme exports that regenerate the bridge file.
{%- endcomment -%}

<style>
  .template-article .rte a,
  .template-article .inline-rte a {
    color: #962F80 !important;
  }
  .template-article .rte a:hover,
  .template-article .inline-rte a:hover {
    color: #6E2460 !important;
  }
</style>
